        {
            "level": "Introduction", 
            "headline": "Create Layers in a Photo", 
            "time": "5-10 Minutes", 
            "exampleMediaPath": "1.jpg", 
            "type": "IntroCard", 
            "id": "intro_card_0"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Layers help the two dimensional space of a photograph better represent the three-dimensional world.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_0"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To create depth in a photo, compose in distinct layers: foreground and background. Sometimes a third layer, a middle ground, is used.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_1"
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "3.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "TK", 
            "exampleMediaPath": "3.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_0"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The main subject of your photo can be a person or an object. It should be placed on one distinct layer of the frame.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_2"
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "4.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "In this photo the foreground is in color.", 
            "exampleMediaPath": "4.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The second layer, often the background layer, can be composed to help the viewer better understand a subject's environment and more about the story.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_3"
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "5.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "In this photo, the background is in color", 
            "exampleMediaPath": "5.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The most basic application of this idea for photojournalism is to create two distinct layers: a subject layer and a second layer that provides context to the story.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_4"
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "0.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "In this photo the subject layer is in color.", 
            "exampleMediaPath": "0.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_3"
        }, 
        {
            "type": "TipCard", 
            "id": "tip_card_0", 
            "tags": [
                "general"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Sometimes it can be effective to reverse the subject and context layers.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_5"
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "8.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "You can emphasize the context of your story in an image through where you place the layer.", 
            "exampleMediaPath": "8.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Complex photographs may have three layers, each illustrating a different element of the story.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_6"
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "0.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "TK.", 
            "exampleMediaPath": "0.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_5"
        }, 
        {
            "type": "TipCard", 
            "id": "tip_card_1", 
            "tags": [
                "layers"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Next, see if you can create photos that use layers to improve your composition.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_7"
        }, 
